name: Boston Juvenile Court
description:
The Suffolk County Juvenile Court in Boston serves Brighton, Charlestown, Roxbury and South Boston for delinquency, harassment, and criminal cases. Care and protection, child requiring assistance (CRA) and jury trials for all sessions in Suffolk County are held here.

The mailing address for this court is:

24 New Chardon St., P.O. Box 9663, Boston, MA 02114

Care and protection, child requiring assistance and jury trials for all sessions are heard in the Boston session.  Substance abuse and mental Illness cases are heard in all sites within the Suffolk County Juvenile Court.
